node.text:
The most affected region by Coronavirus in Italy 💔 Lombardia is located in the center of Italy and Europe. Home to a variety of industries such as agriculture, manufacturing, fashion and eco-tourism. ⠀

The breathtaking landscape of Lombardy is a mixture of hills, mountains, lakes and plains. Its Alpine area is very popular in winter by skiers. Nature lovers are greeted by beautiful shoreline along the great Lombard lakes: Lake Garda, Lake Como, Lake Maggiore and Lake Iseo. ⠀

Stay strong Italy! 💚🤍❤️ #ForzaItalia

Video by @idressitalian ⠀

Always #wondermore

Visit: https://wonderlustcollective.co

⠀
Would you dare to hop on this ride? 🤯

Tag someone you wanna experience this with!

🎥 by @caseycurrie 

📍 Sand Hollow State Park, Utah

Sand Hollow State Park is a state park located in Utah, USA, featuring a 1,322-acre (535 ha) reservoir and an extensive off highway vehicle recreation area on Sand Mountain. The park is near the town of Hurricane.

The park was officially dedicated in April 2003 and surrounds the Sand Hollow Reservoir. Sand Hollow quickly became a popular site for camping, fishing, boating, and ATV riding on nearby sand dunes.

node.text:
⠀
Bear doing it’s best frog pose on the river 🐸
⁣
📸 by NPS Photo/L. Law⁣

How would you caption this? 🐻

When most people envision Katmai, they think of bears. Katmai is one of the premier brown bear viewing areas in the world. About 2,200 brown bears are estimated to inhabit the park, and more bears than people are estimated to live on Alaska Peninsula.

As many bear populations around the world decline, Katmai provides some of the few remaining unaltered habitats for these amazing creatures. At Katmai, scientists are able to study bears in their natural habitat, visitors are able to enjoy unparalleled viewing opportunities, and the bears are able to continue their life cycle largely undisturbed.

📍Katmai National Park, Alaska 

#wondermore

node.text:
⠀
Meet Neron the Black Jaguar - He has most incredible markings you’ll ever see on a feline! 🤩🐈‍⬛

📸 by @thebigcatsanctuaryuk

Jaguars are the largest felines in the Americas. Adult males can reach an overall length of more than 7 feet, and can weigh anywhere from 150 to 200 pounds. 

Their coats color and markings are very similar to the leopard, with a rich tawny or yellow background with large black rosettes and spots. They have larger heads, more compact bodies, and much more powerful paws! 

The Jaguar also occurs with an all black (melanistic) coat, and like the leopard, the spots can still be seen on black individuals. Albino individuals have been reported as well.

#wondermore
